  "text": "Using ideas of Rallis in the theory of the classical theta correspondence [CITATION_1] , given a symplectic space W = W 0 , one can form the larger symplectic space W n = X n ⊕ W 0 ⊕ X * n , where X n is totally isotropic and dim K (X n ) = n, thus giving an embedding Sp(W 0 ) ֒→ Sp(W n ) for each n ≥ 0. Setting V n = X n ⊕ X * n , we may then consider Θ n (π), the representation of Sp(V n ) A formed by the pairing vectors of π with vectors in Θ Wn , and study properties of this lifting as n varies. In this spirit, we prove the following towering property of this theta lift: Theorem 1.1. Suppose that π is a cuspidal automorphic representation of Sp(W 0 ) A . Then",
